<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 4:50PM CDT  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Marion
County through 515 PM CDT...
At 450 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Brilliant, or near Winfield. This storm was nearly stationary.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Winfield, Brilliant, Glen Allen, Twin, Tucker and Texas.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
